{{short description|2012 book by Mark Colyvan}} {{Infobox book | name = An Introduction to the Philosophy of Mathematics | author = [[Mark Colyvan]] | image = | subject = [[Philosophy of mathematics]] | published = 2012 | publisher = [[Cambridge University Press]] | pages = 200 pp. | isbn = 9780521533416 }}
'''''An Introduction to the Philosophy of Mathematics''''' is a 2012 book by [[Mark Colyvan]] in which he offers an introduction to the [[philosophy of mathematics]] with a focus on contemporary debates including [[Mathematical realism|realism]]/[[Mathematical anti-realism|anti-realism]], [[mathematical explanation]], the limits of mathematics, the significance of [[mathematical notation]], [[inconsistent mathematics]] and the [[applications of mathematics]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Weber |first1=Zach |title=An Introduction to the Philosophy of Mathematics, by Colyvan Mark |journal=[[Australasian Journal of Philosophy]] |date=December 2013 |volume=91 |issue=4 |pages=828–828 |doi=10.1080/00048402.2013.834950 |url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00048402.2013.834950?journalCode=rajp20 |accessdate=26 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0004-8402}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Soto |first1=Cristian |title=Review of An Introduction to the Philosophy of Mathematics |journal=[[Crítica: Revista Hispanoamericana de Filosofía]] |date=2014 |volume=46 |issue=138 |pages=93–102 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/24367787?seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Irvine |first1=A. D. |title=Mark Colyvan. An Introduction to the Philosophy of Mathematics. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2012. ISBN 978-0-521-82602-0 (hbk); 978-0-521-53341-6 (pbk). Pp. ix + 188 |journal=[[Philosophia Mathematica]] |date=5 January 2014 |volume=22 |issue=1 |pages=124–125 |doi=10.1093/philmat/nkt039 |url=https://academic.oup.com/philmat/article-abstract/22/1/124/1431837 |accessdate=26 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0031-8019}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Baron |first1=Sam |title=Mark Colyvan , An Introduction to the Philosophy of Mathematics . Reviewed by |journal=[[Philosophy in Review]] |date=3 August 2014 |volume=34 |issue=1-2 |pages=72–74 |url=https://journals.uvic.ca/index.php/pir/article/view/13130/4046 |accessdate=26 October 