[[File:LTPP logo.png|thumb|The LTPP has been holding the LTPP data analysis contest in collaboration with the ASCE since 1998.]] The '''LTPP International Data Analysis Contest''' or the '''LTPP Data Analysis Contest''' is an annual international [[data analysis]] contest held by the [[American Society of Civil Engineers]] and [[Federal Highway Administration]]. As the name suggests, the participants are supposed to use the [[LTPP]] data in their analysis.<ref name="Nehme 2016-09-29"/> The winners of this data analysis contest are announced in the early January during the [[Transportation Research Board]] annual meeting.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.asce.org/transportation-and-development/news/20160122-tanddi-announces-winners-of-long-term-pavement-performance-ltpp-international-data-analysis-contest/|title = T&DI ANNOUNCES WINNERS OF LONG-TERM PAVEMENT PERFORMANCE (LTPP) INTERNATIONAL DATA ANALYSIS CONTEST |publisher = ASCE |access-date = Nov 3, 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.asce.org/transportation-and-development/news/20180118-winners-of-2016-17-ltpp-contest-announced/ |title = WINNERS OF 2016–17 LTPP CONTEST ANNOUNCED |publisher = ASCE |access-date = Jan 19, 2018 }}</ref>
==History== The [[LTPP]] database contains the data of more than 2500 road sections across the [[US]] and [[Canada]].<ref>{{cite web ||date = May 26, 2016 |url = https://catalog.data.gov/dataset/long-term-pavement-performance-ltpp-data |title = Data.Gov:Long-Term Pavement Performance (LTPP)|access-date = November 10, 2017 }}</ref> The [[FHWA]] and [[ASCE]] launched a joint effort to encourage researchers around the world to use the LTPP data. The contest was first introduced in 1998 by the [[Transportation and Development Institute]] (T&DI) of the [[American Society of Civil Engineers]] and the [[LTPP]] of [[FHWA]].<ref name="Nehme 2016-09-29"/><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.acpa.org/6289-2/|title = FHWA Announces LTPP Data Analysis Contest |publisher = American Concrete Pavement Association |access-date = Nov 3, 2017 }}</ref> The goal of the contest is to encourage consultants, academics and data scientists around the world to use the [[LTPP]] database for generating knowledge about the behaviour of [[Pavement (material)|pavement]]s and roads.
==Categories== The LTPP data analysis contest has four different categories:<ref name="Nehme 2016-09-29"/> * Undergraduate Student Category * Graduate Category * Partnership Category * Challenge Category (Aramis Lopez Challenge) The first two categories are limited to students. The participants of all categories are required to summarize their work within an article. ==Winners== {|class="wikitable" |- ! Years ! Winner(s) of challenge category |- | 2016–17 | S. Madeh Piryonesi and Tamer El-Diraby <ref>https://www.asce.org/transportation-and-development/news/20180118-winners-of-2016-17-ltpp-contest-announced/</ref><ref>https://thevarsity.ca/2018/02/22/the-road-less-travelled/</ref> |- |2015–16 | Michael Elwardany, Kangjin Lee, Jung Hwa Lee, and Coleman Brown <ref>https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/publications/ltppnews/07janmarchnews.cfm </ref><ref>https://www.asce.org/transportation-and-development/news/20170118-tanddi-announces-winners-of-ltpp-international-data-analysis-contest/ </ref> |- |2014–15 |Xueqin Chen <ref>https://www.asce.org/transportation-and-development/news/20160122-tanddi-announces-winners-of-long-term-pavement-performance-ltpp-international-data-analysis-contest/</ref> |- |2013–14 |Changwei Xu <ref>https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/publications/ltppnews/15061.cfm</ref> |}
